title: PPPP’s Sahid Thaheem wins PS-44 election
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 9 (APP): Pakistan People’s Party Parliamentarians’ (PPPP) Sahid Thaheem has won the Sindh Assembly election from PS-8, Sanghar- 5 by securing 60,385 votes.
According to the unofficial result issued by the Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up was Irshad Zafar Bokhari of Jamaat – e – Islami who bagged 699 votes.
Overall voters’ turn-out remained 48.27 %.
